main event: A civilian reported observing a balloon-shaped object moving toward the northwest at approximately 200,000 feet on July 21, 1966.
interesting points: The object was seen for about 2 hours and described as having a small object attached to it., The object's motion was consistent with a balloon observation., There was no evidence found of a balloon launch related to this observation., The Canadian Meteorological Service reported the sighting and requested assistance in identifying the object., No national threat was indicated and the case was closed due to lack of scientific benefit.
